    description: 'Found 2026-06-19 via live builder exploration (Daemon Prince Armoury). Two separate problems: (1) RULES — "Daemon weapon" (+0 pts, "Select one ability from the Daemon weapons section... Can\'t be combined with Greater Daemon weapon") and "Greater Daemon weapon" (+0 pts, select two) are meant to be prerequisites that cap how many daemon_weapons abilities (Dark/Kai/Unstoppable, each individually priced) a model can take. In ArmoryModal.tsx, the "Daemon Weapons" tab visibility only checks `hasDaemonWeapons` (whether the faction/legion/mark data has any daemon_weapons entries at all) — it never checks whether the unit purchased "Daemon weapon" or "Greater Daemon weapon" first, and there is no 1-ability / 2-ability cap tied to which one was bought. A unit can currently take all 3 daemon_weapons abilities (paying only their individual costs) without ever buying the gateway item. (2) UX — even when "Greater Daemon weapon" is bought from the Equipment tab, nothing on that row indicates the player must then switch to the separate "Daemon Weapons" tab to actually pick the abilities; the two purchases are functionally and visually disconnected. FIXED 2026-06-20: designer chose the inline-selector approach. Removed the separate "Daemon Weapons" tab/section entirely (and its dead legion-tab duplicate — daemon_weapons items only ever live in armory_general + the 4 mark files, never in any legion armory). Added a new `DaemonWeaponPicker` rendered inline directly under whichever gateway row ("Daemon weapon" or "Greater Daemon weapon") the unit has bought, in ArmoryModal.tsx\'s `EquipmentGroups`. The picker aggregates the ability pool from armory_general + the unit\'s active mark (the gateway\'s own desc treats it as "the Daemon weapons section", singular, even though the data spreads mark-specific abilities into separate per-mark json files) and enforces the 1-ability/2-ability cap live ("Cap reached" disables further adds once hit). Added `daemonGatewayConflict` to `isAddBlocked` so the two gateways can\'t be bought simultaneously, matching each one\'s own "Can\'t be combined with X" text. Verified live on a Daemon Prince: bought "Daemon weapon" → picker appeared showing Dark/Kai/Unstoppable at 0/1 → picked "Dark" targeting Malefic talons → cap showed 1/1 and Kai/Unstoppable correctly disabled ("Cap reached") → "Greater Daemon weapon" row correctly disabled while "Daemon weapon" was active → assigning Mark of Khorne correctly expanded the pool to include Betraying/Bloodied/Wrathful alongside the general 3. Known minor follow-up (not blocking): removing the gateway after an ability was already bought leaves that ability as an orphaned, still-listed-and-removable Equipment entry on the unit card rather than auto-cascading the removal — acceptable for now since it\'s visible and manually removable, not a hidden/exploitable state.',
