    description: 'Reported live: a Traitor Guard Sergeant (Plaguehost archetype, champion-tier Armory access, NOT `is_character: true`) could buy "Cataphractii armor" for 76 pts — confirmed against the canonical Chaos Space Marines .ods (Armory of Nurgle sheet, EQUIPMENT table): "Cataphractii armor" reads POINTS="-", POINTS CHARACTER MODELS="76", i.e. `p_unit: null, p_char: 76` — meant for true Character models only. User confirmed the rule explicitly: "POINTS CHARACTER MODELS" means true `is_character: true` units, full stop — not squad Champions/Sergeants who merely have their own Armory access. Root cause: `ArmoryModal.getItemPts` treated `hasCharacterScopedBuyer` (built-in Champion on squads with max>1, or an active promoted variant like the Traitor Sergeant) as equivalent to `isChar` for picking the price column — added in v0.66 to fix a DIFFERENT, narrower problem (single-column "DAEMON WEAPONS" items like "Rotting" pricing as +0 for a Champion). Fixed by distinguishing the two table shapes: a single-column item (`p_unit` key entirely absent from the data — no unit/character split exists in the source sheet) still prices off `p_char` for anyone with access, preserving the original Rotting fix; a two-column item (`p_unit` explicitly `null`, i.e. the sheet has a real "POINTS" column showing "-") now requires true `isChar` to use `p_char` at all — a squad\'s character-scoped buyer prices off `p_unit` only, same as any other squad model, and gets nothing (blocked) when `p_unit` is null. This is a GLOBAL fix (ArmoryModal.tsx, shared by every faction) — affects every squad with `champion_has_armory: true` or a promoted-variant Armory unlock (Plague Champion, Terminator Champion, Traitor Sergeant, Aspiring Champions, etc.) across every faction, not just CSM/Nurgle. Confirmed correct (not a regression) against the Armory header rule itself ("Unless stated otherwise, every item can only be purchased once by each model. Any model with access to the Armory can buy as many items as it wants. Items with a cost of "-" can not be selected.") for the one case that looked like a problem: the "Daemon weapon"/"Greater Daemon weapon" gateway item (p_unit: null, p_char: 0 — same two-column "-" shape as Cataphractii armor) is now ALSO correctly blocked for a squad Champion (e.g. Plague Marines\' Plague Champion), which transitively blocks the whole Daemon Weapon trait picker (Rotting/Entropic/Miasmic) for that buyer too — confirmed with the user this is intended, not something needing a special-case exception. Not yet individually re-audited per faction for OTHER items this newly blocks — flag if a previously-buyable item now shows unavailable unexpectedly.',
