    title: 'Allied detachments cannot select their own Archetype/Legacy/Traits — engine has one global Army-Customisation slot',
    description: 'Systematic Core Rules + Missions audit pass (2026-06-08, task #9 — Allies). Core Rules.txt L1834 ("Allies may select their own Army Customisation options") implies the allied detachment can pick its OWN Archetype/Legacy/Traits, separate from the primary faction\'s. Rules-owner clarification 2026-06-22: desired UX is "add allied detachment" as its own concept, with its own picker, while still counting toward one shared total army point limit. FIXED 2026-06-22: `alliedArchetype`/`alliedLegacy`/`alliedTraitPool` added to `ArmyState`; `resolveBase` (resolver.ts) and `applyArmyTraits` (store/army.ts) branch on `item.factionSource === state.alliedFaction` to use the ally\'s own customisation instead of the primary\'s. UI: the allied detachment now gets its own "🤝 Allied: <faction>" tab (App.tsx) — separate from the primary\'s tabs, auto-opened when an ally is picked and closed when removed — containing a scoped Army Customisation (Archetype/single Legacy/up to 2 Traits; no Holy Trinity/Black Crusade legacy-specific auto-behaviour, those are CSM-primary-only mechanics) and its own unit catalogue, grouped by EFFECTIVE slot per the ally\'s own archetype (e.g. Space Marines\' "1st Company" correctly lists Honor Guard/Terminators under Troops) — same convention as the primary catalogue (SlotPanel.tsx). Also fixed in the same pass: Missions.txt L69-70 ("No allies may be included" in Skirmish) was not enforced anywhere — Skirmish now blocks adding/keeps no allied detachment, and switching into Skirmish with one already present drops it automatically.',
