    description: 'Confirmed a real gap (not redundant with the generic Allied Matrix, as the open question speculated): cult archetypes (Blood for the Blood God!/All is Dust/Ambition for Perfection/Plaguehost/Daemonkin) grant native Chaos Daemons access via `rule.alliedFaction: \'chaos_daemons\'` injection — these are documented as the army\'s OWN units (no [Allied] badge, share the AOP — see SlotPanel.tsx), tagged `factionSource: \'chaos_daemons\'` on the roster entry. The mandatory-AOP-minimum check (validators.ts ~805-821) excludes allied units via `getSlotUsage(..., state.alliedFaction, countAllied=false, ...)`, but `state.alliedFaction` is the SEPARATE manual "Allied Detachment" selection (store/army.ts setAlliedFaction) — never auto-synced from the active archetype\'s `rule.alliedFaction`. So `factionSource === \'chaos_daemons\'` units never matched `state.alliedFaction` (left undefined) and were counted as ordinary main-faction units — meaning a cult-archetype Daemon HQ could satisfy "need at least 1 HQ", directly violating "Daemons can\'t fill mandatory AOP selections" (digest §4b Summoning). Fix: extended `getSlotUsage` with an `excludeFactionSources` param and, for CSM armies only, always exclude `factionSource === \'chaos_daemons\'` units from the mandatory-min `rawUsed` count — except under the Daemonkin archetype, which explicitly "ignores Summoning" (and whose own ≥1-HQ-from-each-codex rule requires the Daemon HQ to count).',
